org.apache.karaf.shell.api.action.lifecycle

Interface Manager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ManagerImpl

    public interface Manager

    The Manager service can be used to programmatically register Actions or Completers.

    Registered objects must be annotated with the Service annotation.

    Objects will be registered in the Registry associated with this Manager.

    See Also:
    Registry, Service

    • Method Detail

      • register

        void register(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Register a service. If the given class is an Action, a Command will be created and registered, else, an instance of the class will be created, injected and registered.
        Parameters:
        clazz - the Action class to register.

      • unregister

        void unregister(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Unregister a previously registered class.
        Parameters:
        clazz - the Action class to unregister.
